> So, after changing your scope, did you see that we're spending less time 
> in LinkScoper or was there no noticeable change (I'd expect big 
> difference between DSF and SurtPrefixScope)?

outweigh the difference between DomainScope and SurtPrefixScope.  I'm still using 
DomainSensitiveFrontier w/ SurtPrefixScope.  Originall was using DomainScope w/ DSF.


> How many total documents downloaded (5.0 * 29 * 3600 = 1/2 million 
> docs)/discovered?  If so, thats low.  You shouldn't be using CPU as you 
> describe below -- not by our experience (Unless you are swapping?).

> being written across NFS?  Whats I/O loading like on these machines?

NO other activity to that entire drive but Heritrix.  However, ALL activity is going to that 
drive, including arcs, states, logs, etc.  The load averages on these machines are much 
more reasonable; however, they've also slowdown.  Same order.xml's as the OS/X 
machines -- if that'd help, let me know.
